<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Addition to Expansion of.......(possible debate topic)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Zariin">Zariin</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:59 p.m. 12/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Addition to Expansion of.......(possible debate topic)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=822" TARGET=_self>Expansion of #1</A> (Zariin)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>The idea below is mutually exclusive to the upcoming possibility of no Exp loss due to PvP. One or the other. The two together are entirely too much. Most PvP advocates claim they love PvP due to the extra "challenge."

<P>Combining the lack of Exp loss with the luxury of returned items would make pansies of PvP.
<P>Which would you rather have?
<P>Zariin
<P>&gt; Since I feel that only #1 of the given choices contains the seed
<BR>&gt; of a possible solution, I will comment only on that one...
<P>&gt; When you die, the player that killed you (or 1 member of the
<BR>&gt; group that killed you) can loot one item. All remaining items
<BR>&gt; appear on your body... after 5 minutes per level . This would
<BR>&gt; apply to ANY death ONLY on the PvP server. On regular servers
<BR>&gt; this would apply ONLY to deaths in which a player caused 51% or
<BR>&gt; more of the damage that caused death.
<P>&gt; Higher level players "should" have spare equipment in
<BR>&gt; the bank, hence their longer wait period to retrieve original
<BR>&gt; belongings if they were not prepared enough to be able to
<BR>&gt; re-equip in order to "safely" venture back for their
<BR>&gt; l3wT :)
<P>&gt; The "5 minutes" could be scalable at higher levels,
<BR>&gt; since I dislike the idea of a level 40 player having to wait
<BR>&gt; 3.33 hours to retrieve heavily guarded or ortherwise inacessible
<BR>&gt; equipment.
<P>&gt; Just another thought thrown out there,
<BR>&gt; Zariin
<P>&gt; Two good ways to solve this problem:
<P>&gt; #1 When you die, the player that killed you (or group) can loot
<BR>&gt; one item. All remaining items appear on your body when you
<BR>&gt; ressurect (advantage of being PvP).
<P>&gt; #2 You can use the /consent function to let a friend loot it. Ok
<BR>&gt; if you have blue players who can loot you, but no help at all on
<BR>&gt; a PvP server.
<P>&gt; #3 You are immune to attacks for X minutes after you return from
<BR>&gt; the dead unless you attack another player first. Upon looting
<BR>&gt; your corpse you have 3 minutes remaining of immunity before you
<BR>&gt; can be attacked again (so you can run for the zone).
<P>&gt; #2 is the existing system but won't work for the PvP server. I
<BR>&gt; prefer #1 but Verant might think that is favoring PVP players
<BR>&gt; too much to give them their items back (or it's not realistic
<BR>&gt; enough). I think #1 would be simpler to implement and solves the
<BR>&gt; problem thoroughly.
<P>&gt; Note don't anyone even bother posting that camping is a good
<BR>&gt; feature or I'll whip out my Flame Thrower!
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
